The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Diamond show

 New Delhi, Sept. 26: If you want to gawp at a 184.75-carat diamond that the last Nizam of Hyderabad found rolled up in a shoe and used as a paperweight, just drop by at the National Museum. 

 Osman Ali Khans Jacob diamond, estimated to be worth Rs 400 crore, is on display as part of the Nizams jewellery. The last Nizam apparently found the diamond rolled up in a shoe, the Indian Council for Cultural Relations chairman, Karan Singh, said.




